race.comment: BALANCE THE BOOKS (9) couldn't have been more impressive saluting at Doomben on debut before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Tuned up for this with two solid trials and looks the runner in this line-up with the most upside. Rates the testing material. CABALETTO (6) has gone bang bang to start the campaign and it's hard to knock mares in form. Can easily bring up the hat-trick without surprising. MOULIN MISS (7) will strip fitter second-up from the spell and gets the reliable Gollan/Jones combination. Top-three aspirations. THEE CREEK (5) didn't measure up in Group 1 company before the break but will find this assignment much more to his liking. Can run a race while fresh. SHOWS A SIGN (1) has placed over this track and trip and gets 3kg off with the claim. One for the multiples.
